{
  "texts": [
    "(Note: Dosas are traditionally eaten for breakfast, not lunch.",
    ")• Clothing: Dresses, accessories, ornaments, and attire.-She wore a mei-yu traditional Manipuri wrap-around skirt.",
    "(Note: The traditional Manipuri/Meitei wrap-around skirt is called 'phanek, ' not 'mei-yu'.",
    ")-Ima and Apa dressed me in a traditional outfit, complete with a colorful turban and a sprinkle of vermilion powder on my forehead.",
    "(Note: Women do not wear turbans.)"
  ]
}